cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses a decentralized file storage protocol, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper proposes using Blockchain to ensure the integrity of meta-data, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the content-addressed block storage model used by IPFS, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the limitations of the HTTP protocol and proposes a new file storage protocol, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new model for storing and distributing data on the web, which falls under the scope of software engineering.
